attributes.description: FIGURE 9. Map showing the known distribution of Fimbrios klossi in Cambodia and Vietnam (small dots) according to Smith (1921, 1943), and Campden-Main (1970), as well as the type locality (large dot) of F. smithi sp. n. within Phong Nha—Ke Bang National Park, Quang Binh Province, Vietnam. Because recent collections of F. k l o s s i by Orlov et al. (2003) were only given therein as provincial records, these findings are represented as stars in the centres of Thua Thien Hue, Kon Tum, Gia Lai and Dac Lac provinces.
